    {
      "id": "BYtC",
      "code_hash": "15bb8c2c571bc7b0cf66ef37aaa36e49",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h2 id=\"key-insights\">Key Insights</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Syria's refugee population exploded from near zero in 2011 to over 6.5 million by 2016, making it the world's largest source of refugees</li>\n<li>Afghanistan has been a top-3 refugee source for over two decades, with numbers climbing back above 6 million after the 2021 Taliban takeover</li>\n<li>Ukraine generated the fastest-ever refugee crisis, surging from negligible numbers to over 6 million in a single year (2022)</li>\n<li>South Sudan and Myanmar each produced over a million refugees following civil conflict and military coups</li>\n</ul></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
